Recommendations for Your 100GB VM
Since you have 100GB, you have roughly 50GB of "breathing room." Here are a few tips to keep it lean:
•	Prune Docker: Occasionally run docker system prune to remove old Milvus containers or unused volumes.
•	Monitor the HF Cache: If you notice your space dropping, check the HuggingFace cache folder. You can set the environment variable HF_HOME to a specific partition if you add more disks later.
•	Use Virtual Environments: Keep your LangChain/LlamaIndex projects in a venv or conda environment to prevent dependency bloat in the system Python.



