3/19/2026 – Embedding Model

1. Embeddings: Turning Ideas into Math
An LLM doesn't "read" words like a human. Instead, it uses an Embedding Model to convert text into a long list of numbers called a Vector.
•	Semantic Proximity: If you plot these numbers on a map, words with similar meanings end up close together.
•	Example: In a 2D map, the vector for "Red Hat Linux" would be geographically very close to "CentOS" or "Fedora," but very far away from "Baking Recipes."

